# Backend Blueprint

Document backend apps/modules, route groups, service rules/logic, schema ownership, and integration boundaries.

## Services and Rules
- Add app/service responsibilities and business rules.
- `booking/views/api_v1.py` owns booking-scoped support mutations:
  - reviews only when `booking_status` is `Completed`, `Closed`, or `Close`
  - complaints only when `booking_status` is `Pending`, `Completed`, `Active`, `Closed`, or `Close`
  - requests only when `booking_status` is `Completed`, `Active`, or `Closed`
  - objection responses only when `booking_status` is `Objection`
- `booking/views/support.py` owns authenticated current-user complaint/request history lists under `/api/v1/users/me/*`.
- Phase 3 changed frontend consumers only; backend rules and endpoints stayed unchanged while the web panel was aligned to these existing status gates.
